name: Big LA's Liquor Store
details: Across the street from Pam's Gift Shop.

name: Bristol Cellars
details: Located on Cupid's Cay, also called Bacardi's due to the giant logo on the facade, known for their wine selection.

name: Burrow's One Stop Liquors
details: Recently relocated from up the hill, now next to Burrow's grocery store.

name: Butler and Sands
details: Near the Shell station in town, next to the First Caribbean Bank.

name: Gene's Bay Liquor Store
details: The last chance to pick up alcohol on the way to the dry island of Spanish Wells.

name: Jimmy's
details: Across the street from the North Eleuthera Airport, perfect for passing time before a flight. Open Mon-Sat, 10a-7p, Visa/MC accepted. http://www.bahamianbrewery.com

name: Mr. Bones Wine and Spirits
details: Located behind the graveyard, turn East at the intersection just North of Pam's Gift Shop.

name: Pyfrom's Liquor Store
details: Easily found and often used as a landmark for travel due to the bright yellow on the building. A good selection of beer and liquor.

name: Ronnie's Hi-D Way
details: Liquor Store, Sports Bar, and Smoke Shop. Live music on select nights.

name: North Eleuthera Airport
details: The northernmost airport, ELH, receives the majority of the foreign visitors to the island. Outside of the terminal, taxi service to Harbour Island water transport is readily available. Across the street you will find snacks and beverages.

name: Governor's Harbour Airport
details: The central airport, GHB, is closest to most vehicle rental agents and generally allows avoidance of car delivery fees. Some snacks are available inside the terminal, while a bar is just outside.

name: Rock Sound Airport
details: The southernmost airport, RSD, receives the least amount of foreign travelers.

name: Three Islands Dock
details: Water taxi transportation to Harbour Island Government Dock. Rates are $5 per person and are readily available during the daylight hours.

name: Harbour Island Government Dock
details: Water taxi transportation to Three Islands Dock on Eleuthera. Rates are $5 per person and are readily available during the daylight hours.

name: Gene's Bay Dock
details: Sometimes spelled 'Jean's,' this Northwest dock provides water taxi transportation to Spanish Wells for $5 per passenger.

name: Spanish Wells Dock
details: Water taxi dock for return transportation to Gene's Bay Dock.

name: Governor's Harbour Ferry Dock
details: Landing point for the Bahamas Fast Ferries serving Nassau.

name: Davis Harbour Marina
details: Though it's called Davis Harbour @ Cotton Bay, this marina is actually on the 'Caribbean' side of the island, about 2 miles Southwest of Cotton Bay. http://www.discovercottonbay.com/marina.html.

name: Da Perk
details: The only coffee shop on the island, also serves sandwiches and snacks. Indoor/outdoor seating, air-conditioned.

name: North Eleuthera Shopping Center
details: One of the largest grocery stores on the island, also called Burchies. Mon-Thu 8am-8pm, Fri-Sat 8am-9pm, Sun 7am-10am

name: Island Farm
details: The best source for fresh fruit, vegetables, spices, and on select days breads. Open Mon-Sat 9am-4pm www.islandfarmeleuthera.com

name: The Laughing Lizard Cafe
details: $$, Open Mon-Sat, L, soup, salad, and sandwiches

name: The Bistro
details: Elegant beachfront dining room and bar. Serves breakfast, lunch, and dinner from an American style menu. Bar features swim-up seating from the infinity pool. Covered seating in dining room and bar.

name: Banks Road Deli
details: Featuring meats and cheeses to take home, as well as sandwiches and other light fare. The deli shares space with the Pineapple Fields front desk and also contains some of their branded merchandise.

name: The Beach House Restaurant & Tapas Bar
The Rainbow Inn Seafood, Steakhouse & Bar
Pascal's Caribbean Fusion
details: Located at the 4 Points Marina Village, Pascal's offers traditional and eclectic plates with prime water views at tables or the large bar. Serves lunch and dinner.

name: Sammy's Place
details: Affordable breakfast, lunch, and dinner options are available at Sammy for dine-in or carry-out. Popular for picnic lunches at Southern beaches.

name: Governor's Harbour Boat Ramp
details: Buy the catch of the day when the fishermen return around 3PM.

name: Tarpum Bay Fishing Dock
details: Buy the catch of the day when the fishermen return around 3PM.

name: James Cistern Pier
details: Buy the catch of the day when the fishermen return around 3PM.

name: Pam's Island Made Gifts
details: Mon-Sat, 9am-5pm, island paintings, ornaments, sauces, and numerous souvenirs of Eleuthera. Typically carries a great road map.

name: The Beach House Gift Shop
details: Mon-Sat, 9am-5pm, island paintings, ornaments, sauces, and the best map of Eleuthera.

name: Cocodimama
details: Currently closed during renovations, seaside hotel is available for private rentals during construction.

name: Sky Beach Club
details: Luxurious multi-bedroom villas and romantic bungalows with ocean views. Infinity pool, restaurant and bar on-site. www.skybeachclub.com

name: Unique Village
details: Tippy's serve awesome and overpriced food

name: Forty’s Sports and Rental Shop
details: Rents kayaks, bikes, and arranges fishing trips.

name: Clearwater Dive Shop
details: Rents snorkel equipment, oxygen tanks, and Hawaiian slings.

name: Ocean Fox - Davis Harbour
details: Scuba and snorkel equipment rentals, training, and charters.

name: Ocean Fox - Harbour Island
details: Scuba and snorkel equipment rentals, training, and charters.

name: Valentine's Dive Shop
details: Scuba and snorkel equipment rentals, training, and charters.

name: Glass Window Bridge
details: Formerly the narrowest land bridge in the world, the rebuilt road crosses the point where the deep raging Atlantic waters meet the calm shallow water of the Great Bahama Bank.

name: Queen's Bath
details: Located adjacent to the Cow & Bull rock formation, the Queen's Bath's are shallow pools of water found at low tide that offer a place to cool off, and an unbeatable view.

name: Cow & Bull
details: A rock formation overlooking the ocean. Erosion has given them their bovine-like shapes, further highlighted by a distinct roar through the air on a windy day.

name: Rainbow Cliffs
details: Towering cliffs over the Atlantic form a wave like pattern along the coast. Known for it's cliff diving (use caution) and natural infinity pools formed at low tide.

name: Gusty's
details: Tippy's serve awesome and overpriced food

name: VicHum's
details: Tippy's serve awesome and overpriced food
